-- Nokia Profit Falls More Than Analysts Estimated
-- Vidya Root
-- 2010-07-22T10:04:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/nokia-net-drops-more-than-estimated-40-on-competition-from-apple-google.html

          
          
             Nokia Oyj, the world’s biggest maker
of mobile phones, posted a steeper-than-expected 40 percent drop
in second-quarter profit on competition from Apple Inc.’s iPhone
and devices based on Google Inc.’s Android software.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     Nokia's E72 mobile handset is held by a customer at a Phones 4u store in London. Photographer: Simon Dawson/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          July 22 (Bloomberg) -- Christopher Nicholson, lead equity analyst at research firm Oraca Ltd., talks about the Nokia OYJ's strategy and management. 
     He speaks on Bloomberg Television's "Countdown" with Francine Lacqua. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
